---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Navbar from "../components/Navbar";
import Contact from "../components/Contact";
import "../styles/global.css";
---

<Layout title="Terms of Service | SynVoke">
    <Navbar client:load />

    <main
        class="pt-32 pb-24 min-h-[80vh] bg-white text-gray-900 border-b border-gray-100"
    >
        <div class="container mx-auto px-4 md:px-8 max-w-4xl pt-16">
            <h1
                class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-display font-bold mb-6 text-gray-900"
            >
                Terms of Service
            </h1>
            <p
                class="text-gray-500 font-mono text-sm tracking-widest uppercase mb-16"
            >
                Last Updated: March 2026
            </p>

            <div class="prose prose-lg prose-indigo max-w-none text-gray-600">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-4">
                    1. Acceptance of Terms
                </h2>
                <p>
                    By accessing and using SynVoke's services, website, or
                    enterprise engineering solutions, you agree to be bound by
                    these Terms of Service. If you do not agree to these terms,
                    please do not use our services.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-4">
                    2. Engineering Services
                </h2>
                <p>
                    SynVoke provides premium software engineering, enterprise
                    architecture, and technical consultation. The specific
                    scope, deliverables, and timelines for each project will be
                    documented in a separate Official Quote or Master Services
                    Agreement (MSA) signed by both parties.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-4">
                    3. Intellectual Property
                </h2>
                <p>
                    Upon full payment of all invoices related to a specific
                    project, the intellectual property (IP) rights of the
                    custom-developed software will be transferred to the client,
                    unless explicitly stated otherwise in the project's MSA.
                    SynVoke retains rights to all pre-existing tools, libraries,
                    and frameworks utilized during development.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-4">
                    4. Payment Terms
                </h2>
                <p>
                    Invoices are generated according to the milestones specified
                    in your project agreement. Standard payment terms are Net 14
                    days from the date of invoice. Late payments may result in a
                    suspension of services and incur late fees as specified in
                    our billing agreements.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-4">
                    5. Confidentiality
                </h2>
                <p>
                    SynVoke agrees to maintain the strictest confidentiality
                    regarding your business logic, data, and trade secrets. We
                    are happy to sign standard Non-Disclosure Agreements (NDAs)
                    prior to discussing any sensitive technical project
                    constraints.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-4">
                    6. Limitation of Liability
                </h2>
                <p>
                    While we strive for engineering perfection, SynVoke shall
                    not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special,
                    consequential, or punitive damages resulting from your
                    access to or use of, or inability to access or use, the
                    services or any content provided.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </main>

    <Contact client:visible />
</Layout>
